// Table (ai-ui display)
// AI-UI table component with client-side sorting, optional row selection,
// and pagination. Columns can be individually configured as sortable or not.

FUNCTION Table(columns, rows, sortable, selectable, paginated, pageSize, ...) -> JSX  EXPORT
  sortedRows: memoized sort of rows by sortColumn/sortDirection. Null values
  sort to the bottom. Strings use localeCompare; numbers/dates use comparison.
  paginatedRows: slices sortedRows to currentPage × currentPageSize.
  IF selectable: renders a "select all" checkbox in the header and per-row
  checkboxes. Selection state is local (Set of row indices).
  IF paginated and totalPages > 1: renders a pagination footer with page size
  selector, "Page X of Y" display, and Previous/Next buttons.
  Shows "No data available" empty state when paginatedRows is empty.

---

FUNCTION handleSort(columnKey) -> void
  Cycles sort: asc -> desc -> null (none). Sets sortColumn and sortDirection.
  Calls onSort callback with the new direction.

---

FUNCTION handleSelectAll(e) -> void
  IF checked: adds all visible (paginated) row indices to selectedRows.
  IF unchecked: clears selectedRows.

---

FUNCTION handleSelectRow(rowIndex) -> void
  Toggles rowIndex in selectedRows set. Calls onRowSelect callback.

---

FUNCTION getSortIcon(columnKey) -> JSX
  Returns an inactive indicator if the column is not sorted.
  Returns a down-arrow for "asc" sort, up-arrow for "desc" sort.
